dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.trans.tp.TerminationPoint
dataStructure.description:
This is an abstract class that terminates transport entities, such as trails and connections. This object class is a basic object class from which subclasses, such as TrailTerminationPoint and ConnectionTerminationPoint, are derived. This object is taken from M.3100. DEN-ng integrates it into the ManagedTransmissionEntity hierarchy so that it can interact with IETF managed objects.

This entity is abstract

This entity is optional
dataStructure.label: TerminationPoint

child.name: endPointLabel
child.description:
This is a string that contains specific identifier information about the data flow managed on each TerminationPoint, for example ATM VP and/or VC, stacked Ethernet VLAN identifiers and so on.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: endPointLabel

child.name: direction
child.description:
This is an enumerated integer, and defines whether this object instance carries traffic uni-directionally or bi-directionally. Values include: 0: Unknown 1: Sources Traffic 2: Sinks Traffic 3: Carries Traffic Bi-directionally

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: direction

child.name: typeOfTP
child.description:
This is an enumerated integer that is used to define the type of this particular TP. Values include: 0: unknown 1: uni-directional, source 2: uni-directional, sink 3: bi-directional, source 4: bi-directional, sink

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: typeOfTP

child.name: vendorTPName
child.description:
This is a string that contains the vendor-specific name of this TerminationPoint. This is different from the CommonName attribute, which represents a system-wide naming structure for all ManagedObjects. For example, an Alcatel CTP might be identified as LG1-STS12CA-13 (line group 1, STS-12, concatenated, side A, time slot 13).

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: vendorTPName
